observations.recommendation:
We recommended to the Management the following: 

a. Mobilize the Inventory Committee to facilitate the completion of physical count of all PPE items;

b. Instruct the Municipal Accountant, GSO, Municipal Engineer and the Inventory Committee to strictly perform their duties and responsibilities in the reporting of Local Road Network as mandated under COA Circular No. 2015-008.

We recommend the management to strictly implement the pertinent provisions of COA Circular No. 2020-006 in the conduct of its inventory of PPE thru its Inventory Committee who shall:
Prepare, in coordination with Property Supply Office, and Accounting Office, and submit the PIP for approval to the Head of the Agency to ensure that the conduct of inventory is properly and adequately planned;
Submit a Copy of the approved PIP to the COA Audit Team at least 10 calendar days before the scheduled start of inventory taking activities;
Properly recognize and account PPEs that are Found On-Station and Non-Existing/Missing PPE; and
Prepare and submit a consolidated RPCPPE
